<subSubSection id="BEF1B39B2653ADECF21502476DD5B23C" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="486174B937EA68BDDC48094C368EEEAD" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">
<taxonomicName id="50D8BB129DF52A8654D9C658A4A0BE1A" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Blemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Blemus</taxonomicName>
Dejean, 1821: 16. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="CE6D2CC847C6145B9B2D37478D64DC50" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1792" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis id="8431D8548B5D7C188320D43289215159" italics="true" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">Carabus discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1792 designated by Westwood (1838: 5). Etymology. Uncertain, possibly from the Greek 
<emphasis id="45A49FF9796F5F3C4014515C46AA3813" italics="true" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">blema</emphasis>
(a throw, cast; a shot, wound; a coverlet) [masculine]. The name was proposed by Franz Anton Ziegler and made available by Dejean.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D669F4491C6C493C7D28E0CA2A2C3A4" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">
<taxonomicName id="E5E438F6715DD1A77857FD510B7EF58E" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Lasiotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lasiotrechus</taxonomicName>
Ganglbauer, 1891a: 187, 191. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="40F121588683BEB08058712804DC8D31" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1792" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Carabus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discus">
<emphasis id="F5B271B96E576128758ACC79DCDD5DE0" italics="true" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">Carabus discus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1792 by monotypy. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="4D357B22ACA38C30D7206568F6EA72B8" italics="true" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">lasios</emphasis>
(hairy) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="EE0CEB83691BB2790631865CA8A1133F" authorityName="Clairville" authorityYear="1806" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E580E581CEB3E0DE800C86D3685548A5" italics="true" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">Trechus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[
<emphasis id="3BE0E26739251B0B3A785954CA0F0C76" italics="true" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">q.v</emphasis>
.], alluding to the densely pubescent elytra (&quot; 
<emphasis id="C04F5470E7227674D9BA479038FA12F3" italics="true" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">
Nur die 
<normalizedToken id="7183398BF3BF27E03DF4D032EFD76F9C" originalValue="Flügeldecken">Fluegeldecken</normalizedToken>
pubescent
</emphasis>
&quot;) of the adult [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6CE361914F15A45E118305ECD2EE58CA" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="905E0DB964D8F47ABD6D4780088A1B60" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="11C6E3C18F006415DF0B533F17A9232A" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">Two Palaearctic species, one of them adventive in North America.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DAAC6B54BA0ADD6442C776E5F5602750" pageId="329" pageNumber="330" type="identification">
<paragraph id="F623AF5353851A287C3CA36311BAF65F" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">Identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="66147978D348A47364E61A26B9517293" pageId="329" pageNumber="330">
The species found in North America was covered in 
<normalizedToken id="BD0ED59ED32F54FC49370A038E74BDE7" originalValue="Lindroth’s">Lindroth's</normalizedToken>
(1961a: 194) monograph.
</paragraph>
